{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_012aAWrYMfkQfuaVs4TQkXhb","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01WvgdDwSQswT6h1S61hFgPS","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/session-retro-2026-03-28.md","old_string":"| **P3** | Clean up `1-1-foo` phantom story from tracking data ($24.35) | CARRY FORWARD |","new_string":"| **P3** | Clean up `1-1-foo` phantom story from tracking data ($24.35) | CARRY FORWARD |\n\n---\n\n## Session Retrospective — Loop #14 (State-Fix Session)\n\n**Date:** 2026-03-28T16:45Z\n**Loop:** 14 (ralph autonomous)\n**Sprint status:** COMPLETE — 74/74 stories done, 17/17 epics done\n**Productive work this session:** None. sprint-state.json desync fix only.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Session Summary\n\nThis session (loop #14) discovered that all stories were already complete. Stories 16-7 and 16-8 had been finished in a prior session, but `sprint-state.json` still showed them as `review` instead of `done`. The state was corrected. No new implementation work was performed.\n\nThis is part of the same recurring Ralph state corruption pattern documented across 36+ prior sessions. The root cause remains unfixed: Ralph's in-memory state snapshot predates story completion and overwrites disk state on each loop iteration.\n\n## 2. Issues Analysis (from session issues log)\n\nThe session issues log contains entries from earlier today covering the code review and verification phases for stories 16-5 through 16-8. These represent the actual productive work done in prior sessions.\n\n### Story 16-5: Rewrite Harness Run Verification Dispatch\n- **Code review:** 3 MEDIUM bugs fixed (indexOf guard, DRY violation, fragile section coupling), 2 LOW not fixed\n- **Verification:** ALL_PASS 7/7 ACs\n- **Tool calls:** 42 (review: 27, verify: 15)\n- **Issues noted:** npm test run twice in verification (redundant)\n\n### Story 16-6: Update Create Story Tier Criteria\n- **Code review:** 1 HIGH bug fixed (false-pass risk — AC2 test lacked Given/When/Then format validation), 2 MEDIUM assessed (no fix needed), 1 LOW\n- **Verification:** ALL_PASS 10/10 ACs\n- **Tool calls:** 34 (review: 19, verify: 15)\n- **Issues noted:** Story test file run 3 times in review\n\n### Story 16-7: Update Knowledge and Enforcement Docs\n- **Code review:** 4 MEDIUM bugs fixed (missing escalate tier test, weak AC8 assertions, silent empty-string fallback x2), 2 LOW not fixed (out of scope legacy terms)\n- **Verification:** ALL_PASS 12/12 ACs\n- **Tool calls:** 38 (review: 22, verify: 16)\n- **Issues noted:** Redundant grep passes, npm test run twice in verification\n\n### Story 16-8: Update All Tests\n- **Code review:** No bugs found. 3 LOW quality observations (barrel re-export gap, line ref drift, missing priority test)\n- **Verification:** ALL_PASS 12/12 ACs. Proof document updated 4015 to 4020 test count.\n- **Tool calls:** 32 (review: 18, verify: 14)\n- **Issues noted:** npm test run twice in verification\n\n### Aggregate Metrics\n\n| Metric | Value |\n|--------|-------|\n| Stories reviewed + verified | 4 (16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8) |\n| Total ACs verified | 41/41 (100%) |\n| Bugs found and fixed | 8 (1 HIGH, 7 MEDIUM) |\n| Bugs found, not fixed (out of scope) | 7 LOW |\n| Coverage | 96.85%, all 158 files above 80% floor |\n| Total subagent tool calls | ~146 |\n| First-pass verification success | 4/4 stories (100% — no rework needed) |\n\n## 3. Cost Analysis\n\n### Current Totals\n\n| Metric | Previous (last retro) | Current | Delta |\n|--------|----------------------|---------|-------|\n| Total cost | $877.04 | $878.31 | +$1.27 |\n| Total calls | 6,381 | 6,398 | +17 |\n| Avg cost/story | $4.11 | $4.12 | +$0.01 |\n\n### Cost by Phase (current)\n\n| Phase | Calls | Cost | % |\n|-------|-------|------|---|\n| verify | 3,750 | $467.86 | 53.3% |\n| orchestrator | 887 | $195.52 | 22.3% |\n| retro | 757 | $103.62 | 11.8% |\n| code-review | 385 | $44.20 | 5.0% |\n| create-story | 348 | $37.05 | 4.2% |\n| dev-story | 271 | $30.07 | 3.4% |\n\n### Cost by Tool (current)\n\n| Tool | Calls | Cost | % |\n|------|-------|------|---|\n| Bash | 2,361 | $290.39 | 33.1% |\n| Read | 1,342 | $185.99 | 21.2% |\n| Edit | 1,001 | $129.40 | 14.7% |\n| Agent | 616 | $80.45 | 9.2% |\n| Skill | 218 | $75.19 | 8.6% |\n| Grep | 451 | $51.18 | 5.8% |\n\n### Waste Assessment\n\nThe retro file is now 4,795+ lines. Each retro session pays to read the entire file before appending. At $103.62 cumulative retro cost (11.8% of total), this is now the third-largest phase — exceeding both code-review and dev-story combined.\n\nThe \"unknown\" cost bucket remains the largest single entry at $227.91 (25.9%). The `1-1-foo` phantom story remains at $24.35 (2.8%) — pure waste.\n\n## 4. What Went Well\n\n- **100% first-pass verification across all 4 stories.** Zero rework. 41/41 ACs passed on first attempt. The dev-review-verify pipeline is effective when story specs are well-defined.\n- **Code review caught real bugs.** 8 bugs (1 HIGH, 7 MEDIUM) were found and fixed before verification. The HIGH bug in 16-6 (false-pass risk) would have silently degraded test quality.\n- **Coverage remains solid.** 96.85% across all 158 files, every file above the 80% floor.\n- **Story 16-8 was clean.** No bugs found — evidence that later stories in an epic benefit from patterns established in earlier ones.\n\n## 5. What Went Wrong\n\n1. **sprint-state.json desync (again).** The same Ralph state corruption bug. Stories 16-7 and 16-8 were completed in prior sessions but sprint-state.json showed `review`. This is the 37th+ occurrence of this pattern.\n2. **npm test run twice in 3 of 4 verification phases.** Subagents ran the full test suite once, then re-ran it (or a filtered version) for cleaner output. This is avoidable redundancy.\n3. **Retro file is 4,795 lines and growing.** Each retro appends ~50-100 lines but reads the entire file. Cost-per-retro is increasing linearly.\n4. **Story test file read 3 times during 16-6 code review.** Subagent re-read the same file multiple times instead of working from captured content.\n\n## 6. Lessons Learned\n\n- **State-fix sessions will continue until Ralph is stopped or patched.** This has been documented in every retro entry. The loop does not self-terminate.\n- **Redundant npm test runs are a pattern, not an anomaly.** Appeared in 3/4 verification phases. A subagent guideline to \"capture test output once, grep from capture\" would eliminate this.\n- **Retro file archival is now cost-significant.** At 4,795+ lines, the retro file itself contributes meaningfully to token costs. Per-session files or a rolling window would reduce this.\n- **First-pass success validates the pipeline.** When stories have clear ACs and specs, the dev-review-verify pipeline achieves 100% pass rates without rework loops.\n\n## 7. Action Items\n\n| Priority | Action | Status |\n|----------|--------|--------|\n| **P0** | Fix Ralph state corruption — compare-and-swap or monotonic version on state writes | CARRY FORWARD (37+ occurrences) |\n| **P0** | Add sprint-complete exit condition to Ralph's main loop | CARRY FORWARD |\n| **P0** | Sprint is complete. Plan next sprint or close out. | CARRY FORWARD |\n| **P1** | Attribute \"unknown\" cost bucket ($227.91, 25.9%) to specific phases | CARRY FORWARD |\n| **P1** | Archive retro file — 4,795 lines, growing ~50-100/session, increasing retro cost | CARRY FORWARD |\n| **P2** | Subagent guideline: capture test output once, grep from capture (3/4 stories had redundant npm test) | CARRY FORWARD |\n| **P2** | Subagent guideline: deduplicate file reads across review+verification | CARRY FORWARD |\n| **P2** | Fix 5 pre-existing BATS failures in all_tasks_complete suite | CARRY FORWARD |\n| **P3** | Clean up legacy `black.box` references | CARRY FORWARD |\n| **P3** | Clean up `1-1-foo` phantom story ($24.35) | CARRY FORWARD |"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":982,"cache_read_input_tokens":28536,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":982,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01J7rgF7H1XXWzrAndxGStgP","session_id":"81cb382a-05ef-4370-9f23-d4277d76c153","uuid":"98393f31-15f1-4a52-95b9-1bbde4970bf5"}
